title: Fix network connection status checks
message:
Fix network connection status checks

We need to specify the type of network (i.e. Wi-Fi) to properly detect
connection status because the device can be connected to multiple networks
simultaneously.

And also refactor some stuff, like store various system services in member
variables to avoid unnecessary getSystemService() calls and use 4 spaces
to indent continuation lines.

title: Fix notification text not being updated
message:
Fix notification text not being updated

After connecting to or disconnecting from Wi-Fi the text of the notification
wasn't updated accordingly.

title: Add alternate notification text for when disconnected from Wi-Fi
message:
Add alternate notification text for when disconnected from Wi-Fi

Instead of showing the all zeroes address (0.0.0.0) say that the device
is not connected to any Wi-Fi network at the moment.

title: Use AlarmManager to check for status updates
message:
Use AlarmManager to check for status updates

The use of AlarmManager instead of Handler allows us to update the current
status event if the app is not running.

title: Navigate to existing instance of MainActivity from notifications

Navigate to existing instance of MainActivity from notifications

title: Fix vector icon dimensions
message:
Fix vector icon dimensions

The icons looked blurry on a tablet. Increase their size according to this
icon reference chart:

http://iconhandbook.co.uk/reference/chart/android/

title: Update UI when debug status changes from outside
message:
Update UI when debug status changes from outside

For example, when an "adb tcpip" command is issued while the device is
being connected via USB.

title: Fix screen lock detection
message:
Fix screen lock detection

If the device screen went off by itself, i.e. not because the user pressed
the hardware power button, the screen lock was not immediately (I think it
can be customized in settings). As a result, debugging was not disabled
automatically despite disable_on_lock being set.

Now the lock state is checked every 5 seconds by the DebugStatusService.

title: Refactoring
message:
Refactoring

1. Use an empty string instead of "-1" to disable TCP debugging.
2. Add getAdbTcpPort() and setAdbTcpPort() methods to deal with
   getprop/setprop stuff separately from the logic behind enabling
   and disabling debugging.
